
Q. How we do Spring without boot -
1. Add Spring JAR dependencies
we can search mvnrepo an search springcontext and add a dependency in pom.yml
2. Create XML or Java-based configuration
in main we create a directory resource inside we create a file spring.xml
3. Create an ApplicationContext
ApplicationContext context=new ClassPathXmlApplicationContext("spring.xml");
4. Ask Spring for beans


//this we find search spring 6 bean configuration xml
and add the beans
now what it creates objects in ioc contaner
<beans xmlns="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans"
       xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
       xsi:schemaLocation="
        http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans/spring-beans.xsd">

<bean id="dev" class="org.example.Dev">
</bean>
    <bean id="dev1" class="org.example.Dev">
    </bean>
    <bean id="laptop" class="org.example.Laptop">

    </bean>
<!--    now it creates 2 objects-->
<!--    now it creates 3 objects-->
</beans>
